The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 600) The first video documentary on the fusion 

 supergroup Shakti chronicles the rise of the band from the 

 early 1970s. Special footage includes Remember Shakti concerts 

 in Paris and Mumbai, the original line-up at the 1976 Montreux 

 Jazz Festival, and rare clips of Mahavishnu Orchestra from 

 1972. 

 THE TV SHOW

 (Cartoon Network, 12 noon, June 25) The classic 2D animation 

 feature debuts on the screen with the journey of Prince 

 Siddhartha, who is prophesied to abandon his opulent life 

 for one of asceticism. Enjoy the film in between the day-long 

 Harry Potter three-in-a-day extravaganza on sister channel 

 Pogo.

 THE STAGE

 (Till 

 July 2) Among the new productions to be showcased at the festival 

 are Blank Verse?s Furrut , adapted from the story by 

 Upendrakishore Ray Chowdhury, at Rabindra Sadan, 6.30 pm, 

 on July 1. The street theatre fare features Jhalapala?s Abol 

 Tabol and Bhool Rasta at the Nandan complex at 

 6 pm on June 26. 




